						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Śingāravallabhasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1327, Pārthiva, Vāiśākha, śu. 5, Friday, corresponding to 1405 A.D., April 4. However the week day was Saturday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of the temple of Śrināgārarāya by Siṅgana, son of Eṟavēmi-Seṭṭi of the Sēnaśeṭla-gōtra, a resident of Penuṅgoṇḍa.</p>						

						</summary>
